    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, then once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pineapple-and-chilli-glazed-salmon-with-avo-and-charred-corn-salsa/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your<strong> salmon fillet[s]</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and spoon over <strong>half </strong>your <strong>pineapple & birds eye chilli sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 14-15 min or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>pineapple & chilli glazed salmon</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pineapple-and-chilli-glazed-salmon-with-avo-and-charred-corn-salsa/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the salmon is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly charred</p><p>Once charred, set aside to cool slightly \u2013 this is your<strong> charred corn</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pineapple-and-chilli-glazed-salmon-with-avo-and-charred-corn-salsa/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>avocado[s]</strong> in half lengthways, around the stone</p><p>Remove the <strong>stone[s]</strong> using a spoon, then scoop out the <strong>avocado flesh</strong> and dice finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pineapple-and-chilli-glazed-salmon-with-avo-and-charred-corn-salsa/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut into wedges</p><p>Chop most of your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pineapple-and-chilli-glazed-salmon-with-avo-and-charred-corn-salsa/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>charred corn</strong> and <strong>diced avocado</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>avo & charred corn salsa</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pineapple-and-chilli-glazed-salmon-with-avo-and-charred-corn-salsa/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>pineapple & birds eye chilli sauce </strong>with a generous squeeze of <strong>lime </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>pineapple dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pineapple-and-chilli-glazed-salmon-with-avo-and-charred-corn-salsa/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pineapple & chilli glazed salmon </strong>with the<strong> cooked rice </strong>and the<strong> avo & charred corn salsa </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>pineapple dressing</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and garnish with the <strong>chopped spring onion</strong>, <strong>coriander leaves </strong>and a <strong>remaining lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
